sub_title: Research MSc Student - Brain and Cognition Sciences | Junior Researcher | EU citizen
summary: A passionate and driven second-year Master of Brain and Cognitive Sciences research student, with a strong foundation in genetics, behavioural paradigms, and fluorescent imaging, in addition to science consultancy in the area of mental health. Seeking an invigorating and challenging master internship opportunity to shift my focus from cellular and molecular levels by embark on a captivating exploration of human behaviour and cognition. I am eager to apply my interdisciplinary skills and excited to contribute to cutting-edge research projects of societal impact that bridge the gap between the fundamental and clinical neuroscience, ultimately advancing our understanding of the complexities of the human mind.
